    <h2>Natural Disaster</h2>
  
    <p>
        In case of natural disaster it is recommended to keep a list contacts. This list should include personal emergency
        contacts, the local police, and local fire department. In the case of water issues from natural 
        disaster you should contact your utility provider. We recommend keeping drinking water on hand in the event of power
        outages and or flooding. To ensure non-bottled water is safe for consumption the United States Environmental Protection Agency recommends 
        to boil water for 1-3 minutes.It is recommended to limit contact with flood water. Flood water may have high levels
        of unknown or hazardous substances. Be sure to stay informed with local news and keep updated on reported damages
        and recovery resources available to you. 
        <br> 
        <a class="link" href="https://www.epa.gov/waterutilityresponse">More information</a>
    </p>

