<div id="freezing">
    <h2>Freezing Temperatures</h2>
<p>
    It is important to be aware of freezing temperatures and what actions should be taken to protect
    utilities. In the event of severe cold weather conditions for extended periods of time, water pipes
    may freeze. A simple prevention method to save pipes is to routinely run water for a few minutes
    throughout the day, or leave a slow drip. Hoses should be removed from exterior faucets and the valves
    should be closed. In the event of a frozen pipe, water should be turned off and a plumber should be 
    notified.
</p>
